Backport of GHSA-p4v8-rw59-93cq / CVE-2026-28223 to wagtail 4.2.3.

Stored XSS in wagtail.contrib.simple_translation: the page/snippet title is
interpolated into the success flash message and rendered through
`{{ message|safe }}` in `wagtailadmin/base.html`, allowing an admin who can
edit page titles to inject HTML/JavaScript that executes in another admin's
browser when the "Translate" action is performed.

Fix:
1. Switch `wagtail/contrib/simple_translation/views.py` and
   `wagtail/admin/views/account.py` from `django.contrib.messages` (which
   does not auto-escape) to `wagtail.admin.messages` (which renders messages
   through a template that auto-escapes and returns a safe string).
2. Drop the `|safe` filter from `{{ message|safe }}` in
   `wagtail/admin/templates/wagtailadmin/base.html` so messages that have
   not been deliberately marked safe are HTML-escaped.

Upstream fix: https://github.com/wagtail/wagtail/commit/1c6f2effed68f4ccad6fbd07987e03641505f863

